green:["Green recovery. The body's primed \u2014 push the heaviest set of the week today, but stop with one in reserve. Longevity training rewards consistency, not bravado.","Today's the day to add one: one more rep, one more pound, one more clean set. Decades of these compound in a way nothing else does.","Your body is asking for work. Give it the kind that matters at 80 \u2014 pull, carry, hinge, breathe hard for a few minutes. Then go enjoy the rest of the day.","Green means earned intensity. You're not chasing PRs against twenty-somethings. You're playing a different game \u2014 the one where the score is decades long.","When the engine is ready, the only question is whether the form is sharp. Nail every rep. The work you do well today, you'll still be doing well at 70."],
yellow:["Yellow isn't a reason to skip \u2014 it's a reason to train smart. Steady reps, full focus, leave 2 in reserve everywhere. Reliability is what builds capacity over years.","Moderate work today. The athletes who hit Centenarian tier did so because they showed up on yellow days too \u2014 not because they pushed harder on green ones.","Yellow means stay in the game. Don't max anything. Keep the rhythm. Tomorrow you'll be glad you didn't try to be a hero today.","Your body's working through something. Respect it: light-to-moderate load, full focus, full breath. The engine builds at this intensity, not at max.","The graveyard of athletic ambition is paved with people who pushed yellow days into red ones. Choose the long game."],
red:["Red means recover. Walking counts. Stretching counts. Sleep counts. The streak counts. Patient athletes get stronger; ego-driven athletes get hurt.","Your body is asking for care. Give it a walk, sunlight, real food, eight hours of sleep. Tomorrow's training depends on today's restraint.","Red days are when 50-year-olds get to choose between being a 50-year-old who acts 30 and breaks, or a 70-year-old who still moves like 50. Pick the second one.","Light movement only. You're still logging the day. You're still in the program. Rest is part of training \u2014 not its absence.","This is the day you choose the long game. Centenarian-tier fitness is built over decades, not workouts. Protect the whole arc."],
travel:["On the road. The program bends to fit \u2014 bodyweight, hotel room, whatever's available. The streak doesn't break for travel, and travel doesn't break the program.","Travel days teach durability. Move something today, even briefly. A walk in a new city counts. Push-ups count. Hip mobility counts.","The athletes who stay athletic into their 80s are the ones who never let travel become a reset button. Today's a maintenance opportunity, not a wash.","Out of routine, into improvisation. Whatever you can do \u2014 do it. The program will be waiting when you're back.","Travel is a reminder that fitness lives in the body, not in any particular gym. You brought yours with you."]
};
